vulnerability.name: USN-5767-1
vulnerability.description: Nicky Mouha discovered that Python incorrectly handled certain SHA-3 internals. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a crash or execute arbitrary code. (CVE-2022-37454)  It was discovered that Python incorrectly handled certain IDNA inputs. An attacker could possibly use this issue to expose sensitive information denial of service, or cause a crash. (CVE-2022-45061)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in Python.
